name: TELKOMSAT 113BT
description: TELKOMSAT 113BT (HTS-113BT) is an Indonesian geostationary High Throughput communication satellite operating in Ku- and C-bands owened by PT Telkom Satelit Indonesia (Telkomsat) as subsidiary of PT Telkom Indonesia (Persero) Tbk (Telkom) a state-owned digital telecommunication company in Indonesia to replace the lost Palapa N1 (Nusantara 2) satellite.

name: TELKOM-4
description: TELKOM-4 is a geostationary satellite operated by PT Telkom Indonesia (Persero) Tbk, the largest telecommunication and network provider in Indonesia. TELKOM-4 is designed to replace its aging Telkom 1 satellite that goes out of commission in 2018. The satellite is based on the SSL-1300 platform, which provides the flexibility to support a broad range of applications and technology advances. TELKOM-4 carries 60 C-band transponders. 36 transponders will be used in Indonesia and the rest will be used for the Indian market. The satellite is designed to provide service for 15 years or more.

name: TELKOM 3S
description: TELKOM 3S is a commercial broadcast geostationary satellite owned by Telkom Indonesia, designed to support high-definition television broadcasts, communications on-the-go, and broadband Internet services. The satellite carries 32 C-band and 10 Ku-band transponders. From its final geostationary perch at 118 degrees east longitude, Telkom 3S will reach customers across Indonesia, Malaysia and other parts of Southeast Asia.

name: LAPAN A3
description: LAPAN A3 is an Earth-observing microsatellite, developed by Indonesia's National Institute of Aeronautics and Space.

name: BRISAT
description: BRISAT (Bank Rakyat Indonesia Satellite) is an Indonesian communications geostationary satellite for banking purposes built by Space Systems/Loral for Bank Rakyat Indonesia (BRI), located in a parking slot at 150.5 degrees east longitude. The 7,804-pound (3,540-kilogram) BRIsat satellite hosts 36 Ku-band and nine C-band transponders. The craft will expand secure banking communications to almost 60 million customers across the Indonesia archipelago, including locations where banking services were previously unavailable, according to BRI.

name: LAPAN A2 (IO-86)
description: LAPAN A2 is an Indonesian microsatellite that carries video and digital cameras to image Earth from orbit, plus a ship-tracking payload and amateur radio equipment. The orbiter carries the amateur radio short text message repeater (APRS) and a voice repeater. The APRS (Automatic Packet Reporting System ) and the voice communication payload is developed by LAPAN using the LAPAN-TUBSAT UHF/VHF radio heritage along with a COTS APRS modem. The primary application of APRS is intended for communications in support of disaster mitigation and relief efforts.

name: LAPAN-TUBSAT
description: LAPAN-TUBSAT is based on the german DLR-Tubsat, but includes a new star sensor and features a new 45 x 45 x 27 cm structure. LAPAN Tubsat will perform technological experiments, earth observation and attitude control experiments.

name: TELKOM 2
description: Telcom 2 is an Indonesian triaxially-stabilized geostationary telecommunications satellite. The 1.9 tonne, satellite carries 24 C-band transponders and spot-beams to provide high-speed communications for Internet, data, voice, and video services to Indonesia, after parking over 118 deg-E longitude.

name: TELKOM 1
description: TELKOM 1 is an Indonesian geosynchronous communications spacecraft. The 1.7 ton, 4 kW spacecraft carries 24 C-band and 12 extended C-band transponders to provide voice and video communications to Indonesia and other regional countries after parking over 108 deg-E longitude.

name: INDOSTAR 1
description: TV broadcasting in S-band; malfunction of 80% of capacity.

name: PALAPA C2
description: 30 C-band, 6 Ku-band; voice and vision communications to a large area bounded by Iran, Vlodivostok, Australia, and New Zealand.

name: PALAPA B4
description: Palapa B-4 was an Indonesian communications spacecraft launched by a Delta rocket.
